    "body": "Hi! Good catch; the code that runs a file from the command line argument is here: https://github.com/ipython/ipython/blob/0845fa68538de8d2843337928b415b96c36c3843/IPython/core/shellapp.py#L389\n\nIt's probably not quite as simple as swapping in the runpy function, because of various functionality that IPython allows, but it shouldn't be too hard to support a directory containing a `__main__.py`.\n"
